data.title: Nasdaq drops 350 points, Dow down 0.10% to 49,432.55, and NASDAQ down 1.57% to 22,788.62. S&P 500 falls 0.88% to 6,884.75. Initial jobless claims rise by 4,000 to 212,000.
data.description: This morning, U.S. stocks experienced mostly negative trading, with the Nasdaq Composite dropping over 350 points. The Dow traded down by 0.10% to 49,432.55, while the NASDAQ fell by 1.57% to 22,788.62. The S&P 500 also saw a decline, dropping by 0.88% to 6,884.75. Financial shares were the leading sector, gaining 1.2%, while information technology stocks fell by 2.2%. U.S. initial jobless claims increased by 4,000 from the previous week to 212,000 in the third week of February, slightly below market expectations of 215,000. Avalon Globocare Corp (NASDAQ: ALBT) shares surged by 123% to $1.14 after being accepted into the Advanced Micro Devices AI Developer Program. Antelope Enterprise Holdings Ltd (NASDAQ: AEHL) also saw a boost, with shares surging by 79%. For more details, please refer to the full story on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Webinar by Xtalks on advanced materials for DNA self-collection in vaginal samples. Learn about improving sample quality.
data.description: Learn about the advancements in materials that can enhance DNA extraction from human samples and aid in the creation of dependable non-invasive sampling tools. Join the webinar to explore how the choice of collection materials impacts sample quality, transport durability, and biomolecule liberation. This webinar is a valuable opportunity for professionals in the field to understand the importance of innovative materials in achieving successful DNA recovery. Don't miss out on this educational event aimed at improving sample handling techniques and ultimately enhancing research outcomes.

data.title: iNav AI tool by Northwell Health speeds pancreatic cancer detection, cutting biopsy to diagnosis time in half.
data.description: In New Hyde Park, N.Y., a study published in The Oncologist revealed that pancreatic cancer poses challenges in early identification, with over 80% of patients diagnosed at an advanced stage. This limits treatment options significantly. Nonetheless, research on iNav, an in-house AI clinical tool developed by Northwell Health, indicates promising advancements. iNav has demonstrated the capability to reduce the duration from biopsy to diagnosis by fifty percent. As a result, treatment timelines for patients can be accelerated, potentially improving outcomes for individuals affected by this challenging disease.
